			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">halt_trim.c is an optimisation for disregarding any trailing HLT instructions so that these are not passed to the validator proper.

However, statically-linked .nexe files do not contain a significant number of trailing HLTs.  (Currently, dynamically-linked objects don't either.)

The trailing HLTs in the static code area are those added by sel_ldr_standard.c in NaClFillEndOfTextRegion().  We don't need to pass these to the validator.  The only reason for passing them to the validator was as a way of checking NaClFillEndOfTextRegion() against the validator, but this is defeated if the validator special-cases the HLTs.
